@node intro "Introduction"

 What is it for?

       Check user new public and waiting mail (Dlglogin.batch).
       
       Diamail offers lots of good features not available in a single
       package before. This is really something what should've been in
       since start.

       NOTE!! Diamail is not a messagearea replacement.
              Do not ever dream reply option etc.

@endnode

@node requires "Requirements"

	Requirements?	

	o Amiga computer is needed.
	o OS 2.04 and upwards. Developed on A3000 OS3.1.
        o Dialog Pro.
        o Dlg.library is needed in libs:
        o T: assign, naturally.

@endnode

@node features "Features of Diamail"

	Features?
	
	o Nice looking scrolling routines. Thanks to Erno.
        o Multiple sysop editable language-files (REG).
        o Moving around the list with KEYPAD and CURSORS.
        o Saves user configuration.
        o Own colours settings for every user (REG).
        o Check public and private mail.
        o UUCP mail check with alias or without.
        o Message read with SPACE.
        o Sysop configurable buttons for many commands.
        o Possibility to delete waitingmail-list.

@endnode

@node langchange "How to change languages"
	
	You need .dat files. I will give them as soon as you register.
        Use editor like CED and change them. Then compile with
        dialog command compilelang.

        Default language is english.

@endnode

@node using "Installation"

   Installation?

	o Copy all languagefiles in dlgconfig:languages/
        o Copy Diamail.cfg in dlgconfig:misc/
        o Copy the mainfile somewhere.
        o Add Diamail in Login.dlgbatch file.
        
	Then test it!!!

@endnode

@node limitations "Limitations (in unregistered version)"

   Limitations in unregistered version?
	
	There is some crippled features. Users (user level below 255)
        do not have ability to change colours. Also I made one
        irritating *UNREGISTERED* reminder end of the program.

        o User can not change colours.
        o You can not change buttons.
        o UUCP check is set to check mail with alias.
          Uumail:<alias> NOT uumail:Janne_Saarme.


	  How to @{"Register" link register}?

   Other limitations?
	
        ANSI-terminal is needed and screen width should be
        atleast 80 and height 22.

@endnode

@node register "Registered"

   Why to register?

	o You are helping me to develop this project.
          Now I am unemployed.
        o Also I have spent lots of hours/nights with this util.
        o Future versions will include more options. @{"TODO" link todo}
    
        What you get?

        o Simple "editor" for changing default buttons.
          Later maybe MUI-editor.
        o Languagefiles. You can edit own languagefiles.
        o User can change colours.
        o You will allways receive latest Diamail by e-mail.
          Ofcourse you need internet e-mail address. If you do not have
          e-mail address, you can get it ANS -> @{"Contact" link contact}.

        I do not like keyfiles. 
        Binary is still quite small so that is delivery.


        Now hopefully reasonable shareware feeds:

        Remember!! No CHEQUES. Only U.S.dollars, German marks or
                               Swedish kronor.


        - 15US for foreigners.
        - 50mk for finns.

	If you send German marks or Swedish kronor, send the same
        amount as 15US.
   
        PS.You may use this version for an evaluation period of 30
           days free. After that period, if you like it and want
           to use it, PLEASE register.

@endnode

